The article discusses the cooperation between the United States and Poland in the field of clean energy and climate security. The leaders of both countries expressed their commitment to developing unconventional sources of energy such as shale gas, renewable energy sources like wind and biomass, clean coal technologies, and civil nuclear power capability in Poland. They also emphasized the importance of combating global climate change and implementing the key provisions of the Cancun agreements. Poland's upcoming European Union presidency provides an opportunity to strengthen the transatlantic energy dialogue and cooperation. The article mentions various meetings and initiatives aimed at enhancing energy security, research and development cooperation on energy technologies, and expanding investments and exports in the energy sector. It also highlights the ongoing dialogue on shale gas development, nuclear energy cooperation, and the development of cleaner sources of energy.